  "summary": "Install-time platform-gated arbitrary program execution in setup.py",
  "details": "During pip install, setup.py's CustomInstallCommand invokes a helper that constructs an argv whose program name is platform-gated: on Windows it substitutes `calc` for `git` while retaining the `rev-parse HEAD` arguments, then runs it via subprocess.check_output with shell=True. The surrounding comment and log line claim to fetch a git commit hash, but the executed program does not match that cover story. While launching Calculator is harmless in effect, the construct demonstrates install-time arbitrary-program execution gated on the installer's OS — substituting any other command in place of `calc` would execute it on every Windows install with no further changes. Additional install-time behavior writes `~/.sqligen_git_hash.txt` to the installer's home directory and runs the bundled test suite via subprocess. Package metadata uses placeholder author identity (`John` / `john@example.com`) and a non-existent GitHub URL, removing the usual maintainer-trust signal.",
